manifests/compute/libvirt/services.pp.message:
This should be disabled when modular_libvirt is true.
Also, we need a proper dependency to stop libvirt service before starting each modular daemons.
One idea here is to define something like

if $modular_libvirt {
  Service<| name == 'libvirt' |> -> Service<| name == 'virtlogd' |>
} else {
  Service<| name == 'virtlogd' |> -> Service<| name == 'libvirt' |>
}

When modular_libvirt is enabled libvirt is stopped before virtlogd. The other modular daemons are started after virtlogd. When modular_libvirt is false then we expect the same dependency.

manifests/migration/libvirt.pp.message:
The following implementation can be simplified using create_resources.

```
$resource_name = $enable_modular_libvirt_daemons ? {
  true    => 'virtproxyd_config'
  default => 'libvirtd_config'
}

$listen_opts = {
    'listen_tls': value => $listen_tls;
    'listen_tcp': value => $listen_tcp;
}

...

$listen_addr_opt = $listen_address ? {
  true    => {'listen_addr' => { 'vaue' => "\"${listen_address}\""}}
  default => {}
}

$opts = merge($listen_opts, ..., $listen_addr_opt)
create_resources($resource_name, $opts)
```

You can't use this because this class doesn't inherit nova::params.

Alternative approach would be make this class inherit nova::params and update default of libvirt_version like;


```
class nova::migration::libvirt(
  ...
  $libvirt_version                     = undef,
  $enable_modular_libvirt_daemons      = $::nova::params::enable_modular_libvirt_daemons,
) inherits nova::params {

  include nova::compute::libvirt::version
  $libvirt_version_real = pick($libvirt_version, $::nova::compute::libvirt::version::default)
  ...
}
```

